HEADWORD: Mastigopoda
<hw>Mas`ti*gop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>ma`stix</grk>, <grk>ma`stigos</grk>, a whip +
<grk>poy`s</grk>, <grk>podo`s</grk>, foot.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Formerly considered identical to the Infusoria, now distinguished
from that group, which has been reordered. See
<er>Mastigophora</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

